## Head-to-Head Prices at Blue Nile

Both shapes sit in a discount range relative to round, but the discount range and grade structure differ. Radiant cut offers an extremely wide price range at 1ct because the shape mixes IGI and GIA certifications and multiple cut grades.

**At 1ct — Entry level:**
- Radiant: [IGI H-VS2 Very Good Cut at $1,910](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26737014?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — IGI certified, lower cut quality
- Princess: [GIA F-VS2 Ideal at $2,141](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27970851?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — GIA certified, better specs

**At 1ct — Mid-tier (H color, VVS1 clarity):**
- Radiant: [GIA E-VVS1 Ideal at $4,560](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28879187?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
- Radiant: [GIA D-VVS1 Ideal at $4,650](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29067559?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
- Radiant: [GIA H-VVS1 Ideal at $4,650](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26558799?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — same price as D-VVS1

**The H-VVS1 anomaly:** On Blue Nile, the GIA H-VVS1 Ideal radiant at $4,650 is the same price as the GIA D-VVS1 Ideal radiant. This is a significant pricing anomaly — H color is four grades below D in the GIA scale, yet both are $4,650. Buyers who understand that H color faces white in radiant cut (especially in yellow gold) capture D-grade transparency at a fraction of the true colorless premium. This is the single highest-value entry point in the 1ct radiant category.

**Size-maximizing play:** [GIA 1.21ct H-VVS1 Ideal radiant at $4,850](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28762246?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — 21% more carat weight than a standard 1ct stone, H color that reads white in yellow gold or rose gold, for roughly twice the price of a princess G-VS2. This is not a direct comparison but an alternative budgeting strategy available in radiant that does not exist in princess.

**At 1.50ct:** [GIA 1.50ct H-VS2 Very Good Cut radiant at $6,980](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27623999?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — a large stone at a meaningful premium but with more face-up size than any 1ct princess.

